text: My first time trying this store. The fried Kuay Teow taste ok but lack of Wok Hey, kind of watery, soft was not oilly, the color was a little pale and not appealing. Their version of Fried Kuay Teow comes with fresh cockles and prawn from S$4 to $6 is reasonably priced. They also serve Hokkien mee, oyster omelette and fried carrots cake.
The kueh tiaw is not my preference... not that kind of wok hey style...$5sgd.. but portion ok la..ingredients not bad.. got prawn
Taste is average, was disappointed that the hokkien mee noodle does not have squid for minimum charge of $4 per plate. Unlikely to go back for 2nd helping
Average fried oyster omelette, sauce could be better.
No wok hey at all and taste incredibly bland. No squid in Hokkien Mee as well. The upside? Not oily
